author: stefan2
msg: Add rudimentary MOVe support to BDB by simply recording add-with-history
instead of true moves.  In combination with the auto-move feature (see
later commits), this will still result in most of these adds being treated
as if they were proper moves.

author: rbowen
msg: Rename: This is more a "tips" section than technical details.

author: stefan2
msg: Add MOVe support to FSX.  This is mainly duplicating changes from FSFS.
CHANGE_KIND_MOVEREPLACE): pro forma declaration of the new change kinds
ACTION_MOVEREPLACE): declare new change type strings
write_change_entry): write / parse the new change types
(fold_change): ... this one; handle moves similar to adds
(write_final_changed_path_info): update move source revs to Rev-1;
(commit_body):  verify moves when finalizing the commit;
(copy_helper): support moves just like ADDs; add extra param checks
